The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Hindalco Industries has posted a net profit of Rs 1,077 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31 against Rs 721.3 crore during the same quarter a year-ago. The sales and operating revenue during the latest quarter stood at Rs 5,010.2 crore compared with Rs 4,784.9 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal. For the year ended March 31, the company posted a net profit of Rs 2,860.9 crore against Rs 2,564.3 crore a year-ago.                             
	Aditya Birla Nuvo Ltd,   part of the Aditya Birla group, has announced a consolidated net loss   of Rs 21.90 crore for   the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2008. The 
  company had posted a net profit of Rs 82.20 crore in the same quarter a year ago.                            
	 Raymond Ltds income for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2008 increased 25 per cent to Rs 445.01 crore from Rs 357.09 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal. Profit before tax was higher by 6 per cent at Rs 30.52 crore compared with Rs 28.84 crore in the year-ago period.                             
	 Bharti Airtel has launched a pilot project in Bengal under which local SMS rates will be 50 paise and national messages can be sent for Re 1. Customers in Bengal can make STD calls to Bihar, Jharkhand, Orissa, Assam and the Northeast at Re 1 per minute. SMS packages with 250 and 500 free local messages along with recharge vouchers of Rs 26 and Rs 51, respectively, are also on offer.                            
	 Jayshree Chemicals has registered net sales of Rs 45.70 crore for the year ended March 31, 2008, an increase of 2 per cent from Rs 44.98 crore during the corresponding period of the previous fiscal. Profit before tax stood at Rs 4.88 crore while profit after tax was Rs 3.59 crore, a rise of 11 per cent and 27 per cent, respectively.                            
	 Samsung will open 300 mobile phone shops in India as a part of its plan to double the market share. The company also plans to set up exclusive showrooms and launch around 20 products during the year. The company aims to double its share by the end of this fiscal.                             
	 Goldstone Infratech has entered into a joint venture (JV) with TF SolarPower and Jusung Engineering to set up solar panel fab in Hyderabad at an investment of Rs 2,800 crore. Goldstone will hold a 54 per cent stake in the JV.                             
	 Tanishq has announced its Akshaya Trithiya offer that enables customers to book jewellery in advance and purchase it on Akshaya Trithiya at the booked rate. The customers have to make an advance payment of 25 per cent.                             
	 Britannia has launched two packs of Treat biscuitsTreat Twistee and Treat Masteez. A 50 gm Treat Twistee pack is priced at Rs 60 and 100 gm pack of Treat Masteez cost Rs 10.
